groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: On Your MARC, Laurel
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: Cache is hidden in the MARC commuter lot of Laurel, MD. The difficulty level could vary, depending on muggles. Parking is available, but will be very limited depending on the time you choose to do your search.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description:
You will be searching for a magnetic cache with room for a log only. Bring your own writing utensil. Please replace carefully!

Logging Etiquette: Geocache hiders sometimes go through a great deal of planning to place their caches. As a result, they'd like to hear your feedback on whether you liked or disliked any aspect of the hide, or if you feel that some cache maintenance is required. Single word, acronym, or emoticon logs may be easier when you have a lot of caches to log, but it doesn't tell the hider or other finders anything about your adventure (or lack thereof) in finding the cache. Please keep this in mind when entering your log. Please also keep in mind that the owner needs to know if the cache is missing. Without DNF logs, the cache owner will not know they need to check on the cache.

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: Not too many muggles around. Didn't see it on first approach but I played hunch and laid my hand on I quickly. TFTC
